org.lenskit.util.io

Interface ObjectStream<T>

  • All Superinterfaces:
    AutoCloseable, java.util.stream.BaseStream<T,java.util.stream.Stream<T>>, Closeable, Iterable<T>, java.util.stream.Stream<T>
    All Known Implementing Classes:
    AbstractObjectStream, GroupingObjectStream, LineStream

    public interface ObjectStream<T>
extends Closeable, java.util.stream.Stream<T>, Iterable<T>

    A stream of objects read from somewhere.

    This interface extends Iterable for convenience; the BaseStream.iterator() method does not return a fresh iterator but rather a wrapper of this stream. It is only present to allow for-each loops over streams. After it is exhausted, any iterator returned will be null.

    See Also:

      • close

        void close()

        Close the stream. This invalidates the stream; no more elements may be fetched after a call to close() (although implementations are not required to enforce this). It is not an error to close a stream multiple times.
